          "tz": 60
        },
        "subject": "LU-4112 obdclass: no yield in cl_lock_free() to avoid deadlock",
        "message": "LU-4112 obdclass: no yield in cl_lock_free() to avoid deadlock\n\nIf an async brw completion is being handled (and rescheds owning\ncl_loi_list_lock!) on the same core/cpu than a thread also posting\nan I/O and thus requiring/spining-on cl_loi_list_lock.\n\nThis problem can only occur on versions where changes for LU-1030\n(ie, \"New IO Engine\" known to \"Reduce loi_list lock contention\" with\nintroduction of a \"per object lock\") have not already been integrated.\n\nIt should also not occur on platforms where cl_loi_list_lock is a\nblocking mutex (MacOS?) rather than a spin-lock (Linux).\n\nSigned-off-by: Bruno Faccini <bruno.faccini@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Idcc8ba3f0b1322f138c9a8963b96d292f4201b9a\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
  },
